result.execSummary:
The defendant Maria L Thayer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Obtain Controlled Substance by Fraud, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.43(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Maria L Thayer in court with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties proceed to sentencing on Ct. 4. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 4:
- Total sentence: 2 years (Initial Confinement: 1 year, Extended Supervision: 1 year)  Stayed for 1 year Probation - 6 days credit if revoked. 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation - apply bail 
- DNA Surcharge waived
- Conditions of  Probation:   Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No drug paraphernalia. Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions.   No use of weapons (e.g. knives, firearms, etc.)  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided.
- Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service and to be performed in one year as a condition of probation. 
- 10 days jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion.
